EnquiryLogs.EntryText:
Test enquiry log 5B.

On 03/11/19 23:50 hours to 04/11/19 00:30 hours in the location of 135 GORDON ROAD, GILLINGHAM, KENT, ME7 2NG, the IP & DP (son & father) were having a verbal argument over washing in the kitchen. Also present were witnesses Obi-Wan KENOBI & Leia ORGANA.IP had a verbal argument with his father (DP). DP under the influence of drugs, whilst IP intoxicated through alcohol. During the argument, the DP was alleged to have thrown a clock at a mirror, causing both to be damaged & shattered glass falling on to a chair underneath, causing further damage, all belonging to the IP.

The argument continued & IP therefore contacted Police to report this incident. DP attempted to leave scene prior to Police arrival and drove his vehicle (Smart Fortwo) in to that belonging to the IP (Citroen C1) causing damage to the off-side front wing.

Police attended the location & arrested the DP on suspicion of criminal damage. DP subsequently conveyed to custody.

End of entry.

Additional text.

Test enquiry log 5B.

H2H enquiries conducted & spoken with Obi-Wan KENOBI, who witnessed the incident of the IP's vehicle being damaged by the DP. Two friends were also present (Han SOLO & Mace WINDU) but they didn't see what happened & only heard raised voices.

End of entry.

Test enquiry log 5B.

Conducted CCTV & forensic opportunities. Statement has been obtained from the IP. Photographs of the damaged items have been captured & recorded in PC 13101 McDonald's e-PNB entry number (M46013101).

DP has been interviewed and provided a 'No comment' interview. Consulted with line manager (DS MOGG) & DP has been bailed with conditions for further evidence capture, followed by CPS charging decision once concluded.

End of entry.
